# Catalog ↔ Collection boundary

## Catalog (`lib/features/catalog/`)

- Read-only universe: brands, IPs, series, figures
- Models use **`imageKey`** (opaque); resolve with **`CatalogImageResolver`**
- Load via `loadCatalogSeedBundle()` (bundled `tools/seed/`) unless task says to use Firestore
- `loadFirestoreCatalogBundle()` returns the same `CatalogSeedBundle` — no streams, no shelf sync
- `CatalogSearchService` is pure Dart; keep ranking/grouping logic out of widgets when possible
- Clone onto shelf only through `catalogTemplateFromSeedSeries` + `CollectionNotifier`

## Collection (`lib/features/collection/`)

- **Source of truth:** `CollectionSnapshot` on disk (codec v2)
- **`ShelfFigure`:** `localImageUri` (user photos), `imageUrl` (catalog asset path / URL) — **never `imageKey`**
- **`ShelfSeries`:** `customCoverImageUri` for user series cover only
- Display priority: `ShelfFigureMedia` (local → cover → imageUrl → placeholder)
- Do not persist Firestore payloads or catalog `imageKey` on shelf rows

## Naming trap

- `features/catalog/models/CatalogSeries` ≠ `collection_domain.CatalogSeries` (shelf template)
- `CollectionCatalog` in `collection/data/` is a **legacy hardcoded** suggestion list — separate from seed JSON catalog

## Do not

- Upload private shelf images to Firebase Storage in MVP tasks
- Add Firestore listeners or collection cloud sync without explicit scope
- Mix catalog search DTOs into `CollectionSnapshotCodec`
